47 ultimix.get_string = function( StringAlias , Default , Value )
48 {
49  if( !Value )
50  {
51  Value = 'default';
52  }
53 
54  if( ultimix.lang.Strings[ ultimix.lang.Locale ] )
55  {
56  if( ultimix.lang.Strings[ ultimix.lang.Locale ][ StringAlias ] )
57  {
58  if( Value == 'default' )
59  {
60  return( ultimix.lang.Strings[ ultimix.lang.Locale ][ StringAlias ][ 'default' ] );
61  }
62  else
63  {
64  for( Condition in ultimix.lang.Strings[ ultimix.lang.Locale ][ StringAlias ] )
65  {
66  if( ( new RegExp( Condition ) ).test( String( Value ) ) )
67  {
68  return( ultimix.lang.Strings[ ultimix.lang.Locale ][ StringAlias ][ Condition ] );
69  }
70  }
71  }
72  }
73  }
74  if( Default )
75  {
76  return( Default );
77  }
78  return( StringAlias );
79 }

1536 {

1538  Minutes = Math.floor( Time / 60 - Hours * 60 );
1539  Seconds = Math.floor( Time - Hours * 60 * 60 - Minutes * 60 );
1540  jQuery( this._element ).empty();

1542 }

1544 ultimix.timer_widget.prototype.on_tick = function( obj )
1545 {
1546  Diff = Math.floor( ( new Date() ).getTime() / 1000 ) - obj.start_time;
1547  if( obj.timeout - Diff > 0 )
1548  {
1549  obj.set_timer( obj.timeout - Diff );
1550  }
1551  else
1552  {
1553  obj.set_timer( 0 );
1554  if( obj.timeout_callback_was_launched == false )
1555  {
1556  if( obj.timeout_callback )
1557  {
1558  obj.timeout_callback();
1559  }
1560  obj.timeout_callback_was_launched = true;
1561  }
1562  }
1563 }

1951 ultimix.dialog.AddOpener = function( Opener , Selector , DataAcceptor , StatusAcceptor , DataSource , BeforeOpenValidation )
1952 {
1953  if( Opener )
1954  {
1955  if( jQuery( Opener ).length )
1956  {
1957  var Items = jQuery( Opener );
1958 
1959  for( var i = 0 ; i < Items.length ; i++ )
1960  {
1961  var OpenDialogFunction = function()
1962  {
1963  ultimix.dialog.OpenDialog( Selector , DataAcceptor , StatusAcceptor , DataSource , BeforeOpenValidation );
1964  }
1965 
1966  jQuery( Items[ i ] ).unbind( 'click' );
1967  jQuery( Items[ i ] ).click( OpenDialogFunction );
1968 
1969  if( jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'tagName' ) == 'A' )
1970  {
1971  jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'href' , '#' );
1972  }
1973 
1974  if( jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'tagName' ) == 'INPUT' || jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'tagName' ) == 'TEXTAREA' )
1975  {
1976  jQuery( Items[ i ] ).unbind( 'focus' );
1977  jQuery( Items[ i ] ).focus( OpenDialogFunction );
1978  }
1979  }
1980  }
1981  }

2543 jQuery.cookie = function(name, value, options) {
2544  if (typeof value != 'undefined') { // name and value given, set cookie
2545  options = options || {};
2546  if (value === null) {
2547  value = '';
2548  options.expires = -1;
2549  }
2550  var expires = '';
2551  if (options.expires && (typeof options.expires == 'number' || options.expires.toUTCString)) {
2552  var date;
2553  if (typeof options.expires == 'number') {
2554  date = new Date();
2555  date.setTime(date.getTime() + (options.expires * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));
2556  } else {
2557  date = options.expires;
2558  }
2559  expires = '; expires=' + date.toUTCString(); // use expires attribute, max-age is not supported by IE
2560  }
2561  // CAUTION: Needed to parenthesize options.path and options.domain
2562  // in the following expressions, otherwise they evaluate to undefined
2563  // in the packed version for some reason...
2564  var path = options.path ? '; path=' + (options.path) : '';
2565  var domain = options.domain ? '; domain=' + (options.domain) : '';
2566  var secure = options.secure ? '; secure' : '';
2567  document.cookie = [name, '=', encodeURIComponent(value), expires, path, domain, secure].join('');
2568  } else { // only name given, get cookie
2569  var cookieValue = null;
2570  if (document.cookie && document.cookie != '') {
2571  var cookies = document.cookie.split(';');
2572  for (var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {
2573  var cookie = jQuery.trim(cookies[i]);
2574  // Does this cookie string begin with the name we want?
2575  if (cookie.substring(0, name.length + 1) == (name + '=')) {
2576  cookieValue = decodeURIComponent(cookie.substring(name.length + 1));
2577  break;
2578  }
2579  }
2580  }
2581  return cookieValue;
2582  }

2626  * jQuery Media Plugin for converting elements into rich media content.

2628  * Examples and documentation at: http://malsup.com/jquery/media/
2629  * Copyright (c) 2007-2010 M. Alsup
2630  * Dual licensed under the MIT and GPL licenses:
2631  * http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php
2632  * http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html
2633  *
2634  * @author: M. Alsup
2635  * @version: 0.97 (20-MAY-2011)
2636  * @requires jQuery v1.1.2 or later
2637  * $Id: jquery.media.js 2460 2007-07-23 02:53:15Z malsup $
2638  *
2639  * Supported Media Players:
2640  * - Flash
2641  * - Quicktime
2642  * - Real Player
2643  * - Silverlight
2644  * - Windows Media Player
2645  * - iframe
2646  *
2647  * Supported Media Formats:
2648  * Any types supported by the above players, such as:
2649  * Video: asf, avi, flv, mov, mpg, mpeg, mp4, qt, smil, swf, wmv, 3g2, 3gp
2650  * Audio: aif, aac, au, gsm, mid, midi, mov, mp3, m4a, snd, rm, wav, wma
2651  * Other: bmp, html, pdf, psd, qif, qtif, qti, tif, tiff, xaml

2654  * Thanks to Dan Rossi for numerous bug reports and code bits!

2656  * Thanks to Richard Connamacher for excellent improvements to the non-IE behavior!
2657  */
2658 ;(function($) {

2660 var lameIE = $.browser.msie && $.browser.version < 9;

2669 $.fn.media = function(options, f1, f2) {
2670  if (options == 'undo') {
2671  return this.each(function() {
2672  var $this = $(this);
2673  var html = $this.data('media.origHTML');
2674  if (html)
2675  $this.replaceWith(html);
2676  });
2677  }
2678 
2679  return this.each(function() {
2680  if (typeof options == 'function') {
2681  f2 = f1;
2682  f1 = options;
2683  options = {};
2684  }
2685  var o = getSettings(this, options);
2686  // pre-conversion callback, passes original element and fully populated options
2687  if (typeof f1 == 'function') f1(this, o);
2688 
2689  var r = getTypesRegExp();
2690  var m = r.exec(o.src.toLowerCase()) || [''];
2691 
2692  o.type ? m[0] = o.type : m.shift();
2693  for (var i=0; i < m.length; i++) {
2694  fn = m[i].toLowerCase();
2695  if (isDigit(fn[0])) fn = 'fn' + fn; // fns can't begin with numbers
2696  if (!$.fn.media[fn])
2697  continue; // unrecognized media type
2698  // normalize autoplay settings
2699  var player = $.fn.media[fn+'_player'];

2879 // flatten all possible options: global defaults, meta, option obj
2880 function getSettings(el, options) {
2881  options = options || {};
2882  var $el = $(el);
2883  var cls = el.className || '';
2884  // support metadata plugin (v1.0 and v2.0)
2885  var meta = $.metadata ? $el.metadata() : $.meta ? $el.data() : {};
2886  meta = meta || {};
2887  var w = meta.width || parseInt(((cls.match(/\bw:(\d+)/)||[])[1]||0)) || parseInt(((cls.match(/\bwidth:(\d+)/)||[])[1]||0));
2888  var h = meta.height || parseInt(((cls.match(/\bh:(\d+)/)||[])[1]||0)) || parseInt(((cls.match(/\bheight:(\d+)/)||[])[1]||0))
2889 
2890  if (w) meta.width = w;
2891  if (h) meta.height = h;
2892  if (cls) meta.cls = cls;
2893 
2894  // crank html5 style data attributes
2895  var dataName = 'data-';
2896  for (var i=0; i < el.attributes.length; i++) {
2897  var a = el.attributes[i], n = $.trim(a.name);
2898  var index = n.indexOf(dataName);
2899  if (index === 0) {
2900  n = n.substring(dataName.length);
2901  meta[n] = a.value;
2902  }
2903  }
2904 
2905  var a = $.fn.media.defaults;
2906  var b = options;
2907  var c = meta;
2908 
2909  var p = { params: { bgColor: options.bgColor || $.fn.media.defaults.bgColor } };
2910  var opts = $.extend({}, a, b, c);
2911  $.each(['attrs','params','flashvars','silverlight'], function(i,o) {
2912  opts[o] = $.extend({}, p[o] || {}, a[o] || {}, b[o] || {}, c[o] || {});
2913  });
2914 
2915  if (typeof opts.caption == 'undefined') opts.caption = $el.text();
2916 
2917  // make sure we have a source!
2918  opts.src = opts.src || $el.attr('href') || $el.attr('src') || 'unknown';
2919  return opts;
2920 };

2926 // generate flash using SWFObject library if possible
2927 $.fn.media.swf = function(el, opts) {
2928  if (!window.SWFObject && !window.swfobject) {
2929  // roll our own
2930  if (opts.flashvars) {
2931  var a = [];
2932  for (var f in opts.flashvars)
2933  a.push(f + '=' + opts.flashvars[f]);
2934  if (!opts.params) opts.params = {};
2935  opts.params.flashvars = a.join('&');
2936  }
2937  return generate(el, opts, 'flash');
2938  }
2939 
2940  var id = el.id ? (' id="'+el.id+'"') : '';
2941  var cls = opts.cls ? (' class="' + opts.cls + '"') : '';
2942  var $div = $('<div' + id + cls + '>');
2943 
2944  // swfobject v2+
2945  if (window.swfobject) {
2946  $(el).after($div).appendTo($div);
2947  if (!el.id) el.id = 'movie_player_' + counter++;
2948 
2949  // replace el with swfobject content
2950  swfobject.embedSWF(opts.src, el.id, opts.width, opts.height, opts.flashVersion,
2951  opts.expressInstaller, opts.flashvars, opts.params, opts.attrs);
2952  }
2953  // swfobject < v2
2954  else {
2955  $(el).after($div).remove();
2956  var so = new SWFObject(opts.src, 'movie_player_' + counter++, opts.width, opts.height, opts.flashVersion, opts.bgColor);
2957  if (opts.expressInstaller) so.useExpressInstall(opts.expressInstaller);
2958 
2959  for (var p in opts.params)
2960  if (p != 'bgColor') so.addParam(p, opts.params[p]);
2961  for (var f in opts.flashvars)
2962  so.addVariable(f, opts.flashvars[f]);
2963  so.write($div[0]);
2964  }
2965 
2966  if (opts.caption) $('<div>').appendTo($div).html(opts.caption);
2967  return $div;
2968 };

2980  opts.flashvars = $.extend({}, srcObj, opts.flashvars );
2981  return $.fn.media.swf(el, opts);

3030 //
3031 // generate object/embed markup
3032 //
3033 function generate(el, opts, player) {
3034  var $el = $(el);
3035  var o = $.fn.media.defaults.players[player];
3036 
3037  if (player == 'iframe') {
3038  o = $('<iframe' + ' width="' + opts.width + '" height="' + opts.height + '" >');
3039  o.attr('src', opts.src);
3040  o.css('backgroundColor', o.bgColor);
3041  }
3042  else if (player == 'img') {
3043  o = $('<img>');
3044  o.attr('src', opts.src);
3045  opts.width && o.attr('width', opts.width);
3046  opts.height && o.attr('height', opts.height);
3047  o.css('backgroundColor', o.bgColor);
3048  }
3049  else if (lameIE) {
3050  var a = ['<object width="' + opts.width + '" height="' + opts.height + '" '];
3051  for (var key in opts.attrs)
3052  a.push(key + '="'+opts.attrs[key]+'" ');
3053  for (var key in o.ieAttrs || {}) {
3054  var v = o.ieAttrs[key];
3055  if (key == 'codebase' && window.location.protocol == 'https:')
3056  v = v.replace('http','https');
3057  a.push(key + '="'+v+'" ');
3058  }
3059  a.push('></ob'+'ject'+'>');
3060  var p = ['<param name="' + (o.oUrl || 'src') +'" value="' + opts.src + '">'];
3061  for (var key in opts.params)
3062  p.push('<param name="'+ key +'" value="' + opts.params[key] + '">');
3063  var o = document.createElement(a.join(''));
3064  for (var i=0; i < p.length; i++)
3065  o.appendChild(document.createElement(p[i]));
3066  }
3067  else if (opts.standards) {
3068  // Rewritten to be standards compliant by Richard Connamacher
3069  var a = ['<object type="' + o.mimetype +'" width="' + opts.width + '" height="' + opts.height +'"'];
3070  if (opts.src) a.push(' data="' + opts.src + '" ');
3071  if ($.browser.msie) {
3072  for (var key in o.ieAttrs || {}) {
3073  var v = o.ieAttrs[key];
3074  if (key == 'codebase' && window.location.protocol == 'https:')
3075  v = v.replace('http','https');
3076  a.push(key + '="'+v+'" ');
3077  }
3078  }
3079  a.push('>');
3080  a.push('<param name="' + (o.oUrl || 'src') +'" value="' + opts.src + '">');
3081  for (var key in opts.params) {
3082  if (key == 'wmode' && player != 'flash') // FF3/Quicktime borks on wmode
3083  continue;
3084  a.push('<param name="'+ key +'" value="' + opts.params[key] + '">');
3085  }
3086  // Alternate HTML
3087  a.push('<div><p><strong>'+o.title+' Required</strong></p><p>'+o.title+' is required to view this media. <a href="'+o.pluginspage+'">Download Here</a>.</p></div>');
3088  a.push('</ob'+'ject'+'>');
3089  }
3090  else {
3091  var a = ['<embed width="' + opts.width + '" height="' + opts.height + '" style="display:block"'];
3092  if (opts.src) a.push(' src="' + opts.src + '" ');
3093  for (var key in opts.attrs)
3094  a.push(key + '="'+opts.attrs[key]+'" ');
3095  for (var key in o.eAttrs || {})
3096  a.push(key + '="'+o.eAttrs[key]+'" ');
3097  for (var key in opts.params) {
3098  if (key == 'wmode' && player != 'flash') // FF3/Quicktime borks on wmode
3099  continue;
3100  a.push(key + '="'+opts.params[key]+'" ');
3101  }
3102  a.push('></em'+'bed'+'>');
3103  }
3104  // convert element to div
3105  var id = el.id ? (' id="'+el.id+'"') : '';
3106  var cls = opts.cls ? (' class="' + opts.cls + '"') : '';
3107  var $div = $('<div' + id + cls + '>');
3108  $el.after($div).remove();
3109  (lameIE || player == 'iframe' || player == 'img') ? $div.append(o) : $div.html(a.join(''));
3110  if (opts.caption) $('<div>').appendTo($div).html(opts.caption);
3111  return $div;
3112 };

4500 function SetCookie( Name , Value , Expiredays , Path , Domain , Secure )
4501 {
4502  if( Expiredays )
4503  {
4504  var Exdate = new Date();
4505  Exdate.setDate( Exdate.getDate() + Expiredays );
4506  var Expires = Exdate.toGMTString();
4507  }
4508 
4509  document.cookie = Name + "=" + escape( Value ) +
4510  ( ( Expiredays ) ? "; expires=" + Expires : "" ) +
4511  ( ( Path ) ? "; path=" + Path : "" ) +
4512  ( ( Domain ) ? "; domain=" + Domain : "" ) +
4513  ( ( Secure ) ? "; secure" : "" );
4514 }

4527 function GetCookie( Name , Default )
4528 {
4529  var Cookie = " " + document.cookie;
4530  var Search = " " + Name + "=";
4531  var SetStr = Default;
4532  var Offset = 0;
4533  var End = 0;
4534  if( Cookie.length > 0 )
4535  {
4536  Offset = Cookie.indexOf( Search );
4537  if( Offset != -1 )
4538  {
4539  Offset += Search.length;
4540  End = Cookie.indexOf( ";" , Offset )
4541  if( End == -1 )
4542  {
4543  End = Cookie.length;
4544  }
4545  SetStr = unescape( Cookie.substring( Offset , End ) );
4546  }
4547  }
4548 
4549  return( SetStr );
4550 }

4651 { /* Calculate the md5 hash of a string

4656  var RotateLeft = function(lValue, iShiftBits) {
4657  return (lValue<<iShiftBits) | (lValue>>>(32-iShiftBits));
4658  };
4659 
4660  var AddUnsigned = function(lX,lY) {
4661  var lX4,lY4,lX8,lY8,lResult;
4662  lX8 = (lX & 0x80000000);
4663  lY8 = (lY & 0x80000000);
4664  lX4 = (lX & 0x40000000);
4665  lY4 = (lY & 0x40000000);
4666  lResult = (lX & 0x3FFFFFFF)+(lY & 0x3FFFFFFF);
4667  if (lX4 & lY4) {
4668  return (lResult ^ 0x80000000 ^ lX8 ^ lY8);
4669  }
4670  if (lX4 | lY4) {
4671  if (lResult & 0x40000000) {
4672  return (lResult ^ 0xC0000000 ^ lX8 ^ lY8);
4673  } else {
4674  return (lResult ^ 0x40000000 ^ lX8 ^ lY8);
4675  }
4676  } else {
4677  return (lResult ^ lX8 ^ lY8);
4678  }
4679  };
4680 
4681  var F = function(x,y,z) { return (x & y) | ((~x) & z); };
4682  var G = function(x,y,z) { return (x & z) | (y & (~z)); };
4683  var H = function(x,y,z) { return (x ^ y ^ z); };
4684  var I = function(x,y,z) { return (y ^ (x | (~z))); };
4685 
4686  var FF = function(a,b,c,d,x,s,ac) {
4687  a = AddUnsigned(a, AddUnsigned(AddUnsigned(F(b, c, d), x), ac));
4688  return AddUnsigned(RotateLeft(a, s), b);
4689  };
4690 
4691  var GG = function(a,b,c,d,x,s,ac) {
4692  a = AddUnsigned(a, AddUnsigned(AddUnsigned(G(b, c, d), x), ac));
4693  return AddUnsigned(RotateLeft(a, s), b);
4694  };
4695 
4696  var HH = function(a,b,c,d,x,s,ac) {
4697  a = AddUnsigned(a, AddUnsigned(AddUnsigned(H(b, c, d), x), ac));
4698  return AddUnsigned(RotateLeft(a, s), b);
4699  };
4700 
4701  var II = function(a,b,c,d,x,s,ac) {
4702  a = AddUnsigned(a, AddUnsigned(AddUnsigned(I(b, c, d), x), ac));
4703  return AddUnsigned(RotateLeft(a, s), b);
4704  };

4706  var ConvertToWordArray = function(str) {
4707  var lWordCount;
4708  var lMessageLength = str.length;
4709  var lNumberOfWords_temp1=lMessageLength + 8;
4710  var lNumberOfWords_temp2=(lNumberOfWords_temp1-(lNumberOfWords_temp1 % 64))/64;
4711  var lNumberOfWords = (lNumberOfWords_temp2+1)*16;
4712  var lWordArray=Array(lNumberOfWords-1);
4713  var lBytePosition = 0;
4714  var lByteCount = 0;
4715  while ( lByteCount < lMessageLength ) {
4716  lWordCount = (lByteCount-(lByteCount % 4))/4;
4717  lBytePosition = (lByteCount % 4)*8;
4718  lWordArray[lWordCount] = (lWordArray[lWordCount] | (str.charCodeAt(lByteCount)<<lBytePosition));
4719  lByteCount++;
4720  }
4721  lWordCount = (lByteCount-(lByteCount % 4))/4;
4722  lBytePosition = (lByteCount % 4)*8;
4723  lWordArray[lWordCount] = lWordArray[lWordCount] | (0x80<<lBytePosition);
4724  lWordArray[lNumberOfWords-2] = lMessageLength<<3;
4725  lWordArray[lNumberOfWords-1] = lMessageLength>>>29;
4726  return lWordArray;
4727  };

5293 ultimix.forms.ExtractFormData = function( Selector )
5294 {
5295  var Items = jQuery( Selector ).find( '*' ).andSelf();
5296  var Data = new Object();
5297 
5298  for( var i = 0 ; i < Items.length ; i++ )
5299  {
5300  var TagName = jQuery( Items[ i ] ).prop( 'tagName' );
5301  TagName = TagName.toLowerCase();
5302 
5303  if( TagName == 'input' )
5304  {
5305  var TagType = jQuery( Items[ i ] ).prop( 'type' );
5306  TagType = TagType.toLowerCase();
5307 
5308  if( TagType == 'checkbox' )
5309  {
5310  if( jQuery( Items[ i ] ).prop( 'checked' ) )
5311  {
5312  Data[ jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'name' ) ] = 1;
5313  }
5314  else
5315  {
5316  Data[ jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'name' ) ] = 0;
5317  }
5318  continue;
5319  }
5320  if( TagType == 'radio' )
5321  {
5322  if( jQuery( Items[ i ] ).prop( 'checked' ) )
5323  {
5324  Data[ jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'name' ) ] = jQuery( Items[ i ] ).val();
5325  }
5326  continue;
5327  }
5328  if( TagType == 'text' || TagType == 'hidden' || TagType == 'password' )
5329  {
5330  Data[ jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'name' ) ] = jQuery( Items[ i ] ).val();
5331  continue;
5332  }
5333  }
5334  if( TagName == 'textarea' )
5335  {
5336  Data[ jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'name' ) ] = jQuery( Items[ i ] ).val();
5337  continue;
5338  }
5339  if( TagName == 'select' )
5340  {
5341  Data[ jQuery( Items[ i ] ).attr( 'name' ) ] = jQuery( Items[ i ] ).children( ':selected' ).eq( 0 ).val();
5342  continue;
5343  }
5344  }
5345 
5346  return( Data );
5347 }

5890 
5900 ultimix.string_utilities.Base64Encode = function( data )
5901 {
5902  /* Encodes data with MIME base64
5903 
5904  + original by: Tyler Akins (http:/ /rumkin.com)
5905  + improved by: Bayron Guevara */
5906 
5907  var b64 = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/=";
5908  var o1 , o2 , o3 , h1 , h2 , h3 , h4 , bits , i = 0 , enc = '';
5909 
5910  do
5911  {
5912  /* pack three octets into four hexets */
5913  o1 = data.charCodeAt( i++ );
5914  o2 = data.charCodeAt( i++ );
5915  o3 = data.charCodeAt( i++ );
5916 
5917  bits = o1 << 16 | o2 << 8 | o3;
5918 
5919  h1 = bits >> 18 & 0x3f;
5920  h2 = bits >> 12 & 0x3f;
5921  h3 = bits >> 6 & 0x3f;
5922  h4 = bits & 0x3f;
5923 
5924  /* use hexets to index into b64, and append result to encoded string */
5925  enc += b64.charAt( h1 ) + b64.charAt( h2 ) + b64.charAt( h3 ) + b64.charAt( h4 );
5926  }
5927  while ( i < data.length );
5928 
5929  switch( data.length % 3 )
5930  {
5931  case( 1 ):
5932  enc = enc.slice( 0 , -2 ) + '==';
5933  break;
5934  case( 2 ):
5935  enc = enc.slice( 0 , -1 ) + '=';
5936  break;
5937  }
5938 
5939  return( enc );
5940 }
5941 
5951 ultimix.string_utilities.Base64Decode = function( data )
5952 {
5953  /* Decodes data encoded with MIME base64
5954 
5955  + original by: Tyler Akins (http:/ /rumkin.com) */
5956 
5957  var b64 = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/=";
5958  var o1 , o2 , o3 , h1 , h2 , h3 , h4 , bits , i = 0 , enc = '';
5959 
5960  do
5961  {
5962  /* unpack four hexets into three octets using index points in b64 */
5963  h1 = b64.indexOf( data.charAt( i++ ) );
5964  h2 = b64.indexOf( data.charAt( i++ ) );
5965  h3 = b64.indexOf( data.charAt( i++ ) );
5966  h4 = b64.indexOf( data.charAt( i++ ) );
5967 
5968  bits = h1<<18 | h2<<12 | h3<<6 | h4;
5969 
5970  o1 = bits>>16 & 0xff;
5971  o2 = bits>>8 & 0xff;
5972  o3 = bits & 0xff;
5973 
5974  if( h3 == 64 ) enc += String.fromCharCode( o1 );
5975  else if ( h4 == 64 ) enc += String.fromCharCode( o1 , o2 );
5976  else enc += String.fromCharCode( o1 , o2 , o3 );
5977  }
5978  while( i < data.length );
5979 
5980  return( enc );
5981 }

6112 // Private: takes a URL, determines if it is relative and converts to an absolute URL
6113 // using the current site. Only processes the URL if it can, otherwise returns the URL untouched
6114 SWFUpload.completeURL = function(url) {
6115  if (typeof(url) !== "string" || url.match(/^https?:\/\//i) || url.match(/^\//)) {
6116  return url;
6117  }
6118 
6119  var currentURL = window.location.protocol + "//" + window.location.hostname + (window.location.port ? ":" + window.location.port : "");
6120 
6121  var indexSlash = window.location.pathname.lastIndexOf("/");
6122  if (indexSlash <= 0) {
6123  path = "/";
6124  } else {
6125  path = window.location.pathname.substr(0, indexSlash) + "/";
6126  }
6127 
6128  return /*currentURL +*/ path + url;
6129 
6130 };

6219 // Private: loadFlash replaces the button_placeholder element with the flash movie.
6220 SWFUpload.prototype.loadFlash = function () {
6221  var targetElement, tempParent;
6222 
6223  // Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
6224  if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
6225  throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
6226  }
6227 
6228  // Get the element where we will be placing the flash movie
6229  targetElement = document.getElementById(this.settings.button_placeholder_id) || this.settings.button_placeholder;
6230 
6231  if (targetElement == undefined) {
6232  throw "Could not find the placeholder element: " + this.settings.button_placeholder_id;
6233  }
6234 
6235  // Append the container and load the flash
6236  tempParent = document.createElement("div");
6237  tempParent.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML(); // Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
6238  targetElement.parentNode.replaceChild(tempParent.firstChild, targetElement);
6239 
6240  // Fix IE Flash/Form bug
6241  if (window[this.movieName] == undefined) {
6242  window[this.movieName] = this.getMovieElement();
6243  }
6244 
6245 };
6246 
6247 // Private: getFlashHTML generates the object tag needed to embed the flash in to the document
6248 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashHTML = function () {
6249  // Flash Satay object syntax: http://www.alistapart.com/articles/flashsatay
6250  return ['<object id="', this.movieName, '" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="', this.settings.flash_url, '" width="', this.settings.button_width, '" height="', this.settings.button_height, '" class="swfupload">',
6251  '<param name="wmode" value="', this.settings.button_window_mode, '" />',
6252  '<param name="movie" value="', this.settings.flash_url, '" />',
6253  '<param name="quality" value="high" />',
6254  '<param name="menu" value="false" />',
6255  '<param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" />',
6256  '<param name="flashvars" value="' + this.getFlashVars() + '" />',
6257  '</object>'].join("");
6258 };

6260 // Private: getFlashVars builds the parameter string that will be passed
6261 // to flash in the flashvars param.
6262 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashVars = function () {
6263  // Build a string from the post param object
6264  var paramString = this.buildParamString();
6265  var httpSuccessString = this.settings.http_success.join(",");
6266

6268  return ["movieName=", encodeURIComponent(this.movieName),
6269  "&amp;uploadURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.upload_url),
6270  "&amp;useQueryString=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.use_query_string),
6271  "&amp;requeueOnError=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.requeue_on_error),
6272  "&amp;httpSuccess=", encodeURIComponent(httpSuccessString),
6273  "&amp;assumeSuccessTimeout=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.assume_success_timeout),
6274  "&amp;params=", encodeURIComponent(paramString),
6275  "&amp;filePostName=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_post_name),
6276  "&amp;fileTypes=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types),
6277  "&amp;fileTypesDescription=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types_description),
6278  "&amp;fileSizeLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_size_limit),
6279  "&amp;fileUploadLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_upload_limit),
6280  "&amp;fileQueueLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_queue_limit),
6281  "&amp;debugEnabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.debug_enabled),
6282  "&amp;buttonImageURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_image_url),
6283  "&amp;buttonWidth=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_width),
6284  "&amp;buttonHeight=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_height),
6285  "&amp;buttonText=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text),
6286  "&amp;buttonTextTopPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_top_padding),
6287  "&amp;buttonTextLeftPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_left_padding),
6288  "&amp;buttonTextStyle=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_style),
6289  "&amp;buttonAction=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_action),
6290  "&amp;buttonDisabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_disabled),
6291  "&amp;buttonCursor=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_cursor)
6292  ].join("");

6295 // Public: getMovieElement retrieves the DOM reference to the Flash element added by SWFUpload
6296 // The element is cached after the first lookup
6297 SWFUpload.prototype.getMovieElement = function () {
6298  if (this.movieElement == undefined) {
6299  this.movieElement = document.getElementById(this.movieName);
6300  }
6301 
6302  if (this.movieElement === null) {
6303  throw "Could not find Flash element";
6304  }
6305

6309 // Private: buildParamString takes the name/value pairs in the post_params setting object
6310 // and joins them up in to a string formatted "name=value&amp;name=value"
6311 SWFUpload.prototype.buildParamString = function () {
6312  var postParams = this.settings.post_params;
6313  var paramStringPairs = [];
6314 
6315  if (typeof(postParams) === "object") {
6316  for (var name in postParams) {
6317  if (postParams.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
6318  paramStringPairs.push(encodeURIComponent(name.toString()) + "=" + encodeURIComponent(postParams[name].toString()));
6319  }
6320  }
6321  }
6322 
6323  return paramStringPairs.join("&amp;");
6324 };

6326 // Public: Used to remove a SWFUpload instance from the page. This method strives to remove
6327 // all references to the SWF, and other objects so memory is properly freed.
6328 // Returns true if everything was destroyed. Returns a false if a failure occurs leaving SWFUpload in an inconsistant state.
6329 // Credits: Major improvements provided by steffen
6330 SWFUpload.prototype.destroy = function () {
6331  try {
6332  // Make sure Flash is done before we try to remove it
6333  this.cancelUpload(null, false);
6334 
6335 
6336  // Remove the SWFUpload DOM nodes
6337  var movieElement = null;
6338  movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
6339 
6340  if (movieElement && typeof(movieElement.CallFunction) === "unknown") { // We only want to do this in IE
6341  // Loop through all the movie's properties and remove all function references (DOM/JS IE 6/7 memory leak workaround)
6342  for (var i in movieElement) {
6343  try {
6344  if (typeof(movieElement[i]) === "function") {
6345  movieElement[i] = null;
6346  }
6347  } catch (ex1) {}
6348  }
6349 
6350  // Remove the Movie Element from the page
6351  try {
6352  movieElement.parentNode.removeChild(movieElement);
6353  } catch (ex) {}
6354  }
6355 
6356  // Remove IE form fix reference
6357  window[this.movieName] = null;
6358 
6359  // Destroy other references
6360  SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = null;
6361  delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
6362 
6363  this.movieElement = null;
6364  this.settings = null;
6365  this.customSettings = null;
6366  this.eventQueue = null;
6367  this.movieName = null;
6368 
6369 
6370  return true;
6371  } catch (ex2) {
6372  return false;
6373  }
6374 };

6423  "\t", "upload_start_handler assigned: ", (typeof this.settings.upload_start_handler === "function").toString(), "\n",
6424  "\t", "upload_progress_handler assigned: ", (typeof this.settings.upload_progress_handler === "function").toString(), "\n",
6425  "\t", "upload_error_handler assigned: ", (typeof this.settings.upload_error_handler === "function").toString(), "\n",
6426  "\t", "upload_success_handler assigned: ", (typeof this.settings.upload_success_handler === "function").toString(), "\n",
6427  "\t", "upload_complete_handler assigned: ", (typeof this.settings.upload_complete_handler === "function").toString(), "\n",
6428  "\t", "debug_handler assigned: ", (typeof this.settings.debug_handler === "function").toString(), "\n"
6429  ].join("")
6430  );

6456 // Private: callFlash handles function calls made to the Flash element.
6457 // Calls are made with a setTimeout for some functions to work around
6458 // bugs in the ExternalInterface library.
6459 SWFUpload.prototype.callFlash = function (functionName, argumentArray) {
6460  argumentArray = argumentArray || [];
6461 
6462  var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
6463  var returnValue, returnString;
6464 
6465  // Flash's method if calling ExternalInterface methods (code adapted from MooTools).
6466  try {
6467  returnString = movieElement.CallFunction('<invoke name="' + functionName + '" returntype="javascript">' + __flash__argumentsToXML(argumentArray, 0) + '</invoke>');
6468  returnValue = eval(returnString);
6469  } catch (ex) {
6470  throw "Call to " + functionName + " failed";
6471  }
6472 
6473  // Unescape file post param values
6474  if (returnValue != undefined && typeof returnValue.post === "object") {
6475  returnValue = this.unescapeFilePostParams(returnValue);
6476  }
6477 
6478  return returnValue;
6479 };

6717 /* *******************************
6718  Flash Event Interfaces
6719  These functions are used by Flash to trigger the various
6720  events.
6721 
6722  All these functions a Private.
6723 
6724  Because the ExternalInterface library is buggy the event calls
6725  are added to a queue and the queue then executed by a setTimeout.
6726  This ensures that events are executed in a determinate order and that
6727  the ExternalInterface bugs are avoided.
6728 ******************************* */
6729 
6730 SWFUpload.prototype.queueEvent = function (handlerName, argumentArray) {
6731  // Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
6732 
6733  if (argumentArray == undefined) {
6734  argumentArray = [];
6735  } else if (!(argumentArray instanceof Array)) {
6736  argumentArray = [argumentArray];
6737  }
6738 
6739  var self = this;
6740  if (typeof this.settings[handlerName] === "function") {
6741  // Queue the event
6742  this.eventQueue.push(function () {
6743  this.settings[handlerName].apply(this, argumentArray);
6744  });
6745 
6746  // Execute the next queued event
6747  setTimeout(function () {
6748  self.executeNextEvent();
6749  }, 0);
6750 
6751  } else if (this.settings[handlerName] !== null) {
6752  throw "Event handler " + handlerName + " is unknown or is not a function";
6753  }
6754 };
6755 
6756 // Private: Causes the next event in the queue to be executed. Since events are queued using a setTimeout
6757 // we must queue them in order to garentee that they are executed in order.
6758 SWFUpload.prototype.executeNextEvent = function () {
6759  // Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
6760 
6761  var f = this.eventQueue ? this.eventQueue.shift() : null;
6762  if (typeof(f) === "function") {
6763  f.apply(this);
6764  }
6765 };
6766 
6767 // Private: unescapeFileParams is part of a workaround for a flash bug where objects passed through ExternalInterface cannot have
6768 // properties that contain characters that are not valid for JavaScript identifiers. To work around this
6769 // the Flash Component escapes the parameter names and we must unescape again before passing them along.
6770 SWFUpload.prototype.unescapeFilePostParams = function (file) {
6771  var reg = /[$]([0-9a-f]{4})/i;
6772  var unescapedPost = {};
6773  var uk;
6774 
6775  if (file != undefined) {
6776  for (var k in file.post) {
6777  if (file.post.hasOwnProperty(k)) {
6778  uk = k;
6779  var match;
6780  while ((match = reg.exec(uk)) !== null) {
6781  uk = uk.replace(match[0], String.fromCharCode(parseInt("0x" + match[1], 16)));
6782  }
6783  unescapedPost[uk] = file.post[k];
6784  }
6785  }
6786 
6787  file.post = unescapedPost;
6788  }
6789 
6790  return file;
6791 };
6792

6794 SWFUpload.prototype.testExternalInterface = function () {
6795  try {
6796  return this.callFlash("TestExternalInterface");
6797  } catch (ex) {
6798  return false;
6799  }
6800 };

6802 // Private: This event is called by Flash when it has finished loading. Don't modify this.
6803 // Use the swfupload_loaded_handler event setting to execute custom code when SWFUpload has loaded.
6804 SWFUpload.prototype.flashReady = function () {
6805  // Check that the movie element is loaded correctly with its ExternalInterface methods defined
6806  var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
6807 
6808  if (!movieElement) {
6809  this.debug("Flash called back ready but the flash movie can't be found.");
6810  return;
6811  }
6812 
6813  this.cleanUp(movieElement);
6814 
6815  this.queueEvent("swfupload_loaded_handler");
6816 };
6817 
6818 // Private: removes Flash added fuctions to the DOM node to prevent memory leaks in IE.
6819 // This function is called by Flash each time the ExternalInterface functions are created.
6820 SWFUpload.prototype.cleanUp = function (movieElement) {
6821  // Pro-actively unhook all the Flash functions
6822  try {
6823  if (this.movieElement && typeof(movieElement.CallFunction) === "unknown") { // We only want to do this in IE
6824  this.debug("Removing Flash functions hooks (this should only run in IE and should prevent memory leaks)");
6825  for (var key in movieElement) {
6826  try {
6827  if (typeof(movieElement[key]) === "function") {
6828  movieElement[key] = null;
6829  }
6830  } catch (ex) {
6831  }
6832  }
6833  }
6834  } catch (ex1) {
6835 
6836  }
6837 
6838  // Fix Flashes own cleanup code so if the SWFMovie was removed from the page
6839  // it doesn't display errors.
6840  window["__flash__removeCallback"] = function (instance, name) {
6841  try {
6842  if (instance) {
6843  instance[name] = null;
6844  }
6845  } catch (flashEx) {
6846 
6847  }
6848  };
6849 
6850 };

6885  if (typeof this.settings.upload_start_handler === "function") {
6886  file = this.unescapeFilePostParams(file);
6887  returnValue = this.settings.upload_start_handler.call(this, file);

6889  throw "upload_start_handler must be a function";
6890  }
6891 
6892  // Convert undefined to true so if nothing is returned from the upload_start_handler it is
6893  // interpretted as 'true'.
6894  if (returnValue === undefined) {
6895  returnValue = true;
6896  }
6897 
6898  returnValue = !!returnValue;
6899

6931 
6932 /* **********************************
6933  Debug Console
6934  The debug console is a self contained, in page location
6935  for debug message to be sent. The Debug Console adds
6936  itself to the body if necessary.
6937 
6938  The console is automatically scrolled as messages appear.
6939 
6940  If you are using your own debug handler or when you deploy to production and
6941  have debug disabled you can remove these functions to reduce the file size
6942  and complexity.
6943 ********************************** */
6944 
6945 // Private: debugMessage is the default debug_handler. If you want to print debug messages
6946 // call the debug() function. When overriding the function your own function should
6947 // check to see if the debug setting is true before outputting debug information.
6948 SWFUpload.prototype.debugMessage = function (message) {
6949  if (this.settings.debug) {
6950  var exceptionMessage, exceptionValues = [];
6951 
6952  // Check for an exception object and print it nicely
6953  if (typeof message === "object" && typeof message.name === "string" && typeof message.message === "string") {
6954  for (var key in message) {
6955  if (message.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
6956  exceptionValues.push(key + ": " + message[key]);
6957  }
6958  }
6959  exceptionMessage = exceptionValues.join("\n") || "";
6960  exceptionValues = exceptionMessage.split("\n");
6961  exceptionMessage = "EXCEPTION: " + exceptionValues.join("\nEXCEPTION: ");
6962  SWFUpload.Console.writeLine(exceptionMessage);
6963  } else {
6964  SWFUpload.Console.writeLine(message);
6965  }
6966  }
6967 };
6968 
6969 SWFUpload.Console = {};
6970 SWFUpload.Console.writeLine = function (message) {
6971  var console, documentForm;
6972 
6973  try {
6974  console = document.getElementById("SWFUpload_Console");
6975 
6976  if (!console) {
6977  documentForm = document.createElement("form");
6978  document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0].appendChild(documentForm);
6979 
6980  console = document.createElement("textarea");
6981  console.id = "SWFUpload_Console";
6982  console.style.fontFamily = "monospace";
6983  console.setAttribute("wrap", "off");
6984  console.wrap = "off";
6985  console.style.overflow = "auto";
6986  console.style.width = "700px";
6987  console.style.height = "350px";
6988  console.style.margin = "5px";
6989  documentForm.appendChild(console);
6990  }
6991 
6992  console.value += message + "\n";
6993 
6994  console.scrollTop = console.scrollHeight - console.clientHeight;
6995  } catch (ex) {
6996  alert("Exception: " + ex.name + " Message: " + ex.message);
6997  }
6998 };
6999 
7000 /*
7001  Cookie Plug-in
7002 
7003  This plug in automatically gets all the cookies for this site and adds them to the post_params.
7004  Cookies are loaded only on initialization. The refreshCookies function can be called to update the post_params.
7005  The cookies will override any other post params with the same name.
7006 */
7007 
7008 var SWFUpload;
7009 if (typeof(SWFUpload) === "function") {
7010  SWFUpload.prototype.initSettings = function (oldInitSettings) {
7011  return function () {
7012  if (typeof(oldInitSettings) === "function") {
7013  oldInitSettings.call(this);
7014  }
7015 
7016  this.refreshCookies(false); // The false parameter must be sent since SWFUpload has not initialzed at this point

7020  // refreshes the post_params and updates SWFUpload. The sendToFlash parameters is optional and defaults to True
7021  SWFUpload.prototype.refreshCookies = function (sendToFlash) {
7022  if (sendToFlash === undefined) {
7023  sendToFlash = true;
7024  }
7025  sendToFlash = !!sendToFlash;
7026 
7027  // Get the post_params object
7028  var postParams = this.settings.post_params;
7029 
7030  // Get the cookies
7031  var i, cookieArray = document.cookie.split(';'), caLength = cookieArray.length, c, eqIndex, name, value;
7032  for (i = 0; i < caLength; i++) {
7033  c = cookieArray[i];
7034 
7035  // Left Trim spaces
7036  while (c.charAt(0) === " ") {
7037  c = c.substring(1, c.length);
7038  }
7039  eqIndex = c.indexOf("=");
7040  if (eqIndex > 0) {
7041  name = c.substring(0, eqIndex);
7042  value = c.substring(eqIndex + 1);
7043  postParams[name] = value;
7044  }
7045  }
7046 
7047  if (sendToFlash) {
7048  this.setPostParams(postParams);
7049  }
7050  };
7051

7054 /*
7055  Queue Plug-in

7058  *Adds a cancelQueue() method for cancelling the entire queue.

7060  *If false is returned from uploadComplete then the queue upload is stopped.
7061  If false is not returned (strict comparison) then the queue upload is continued.
7062  *Adds a QueueComplete event that is fired when all the queued files have finished uploading.
7063  Set the event handler with the queue_complete_handler setting.
7064 
7065  */
7066

7107  SWFUpload.queue.uploadStartHandler = function (file) {
7108  var returnValue;
7109  if (typeof(this.queueSettings.user_upload_start_handler) === "function") {
7110  returnValue = this.queueSettings.user_upload_start_handler.call(this, file);
7111  }
7112 
7113  // To prevent upload a real "FALSE" value must be returned, otherwise default to a real "TRUE" value.
7114  returnValue = (returnValue === false) ? false : true;
7115

7121  SWFUpload.queue.uploadCompleteHandler = function (file) {
7122  var user_upload_complete_handler = this.queueSettings.user_upload_complete_handler;
7123  var continueUpload;
7124 
7125  if (file.filestatus === SWFUpload.FILE_STATUS.COMPLETE) {
7126  this.queueSettings.queue_upload_count++;
7127  }
7128 
7129  if (typeof(user_upload_complete_handler) === "function") {
7130  continueUpload = (user_upload_complete_handler.call(this, file) === false) ? false : true;
7131  } else if (file.filestatus === SWFUpload.FILE_STATUS.QUEUED) {
7132  // If the file was stopped and re-queued don't restart the upload
7133  continueUpload = false;
7134  } else {
7135  continueUpload = true;
7136  }
7137 
7138  if (continueUpload) {
7139  var stats = this.getStats();
7140  if (stats.files_queued > 0 && this.queueSettings.queue_cancelled_flag === false) {
7141  this.startUpload();
7142  } else if (this.queueSettings.queue_cancelled_flag === false) {
7143  this.queueEvent("queue_complete_handler", [this.queueSettings.queue_upload_count]);
7144  this.queueSettings.queue_upload_count = 0;
7145  } else {
7146  this.queueSettings.queue_cancelled_flag = false;
7147  this.queueSettings.queue_upload_count = 0;
7148  }
7149  }
7150  };

7152 /*
7153  Speed Plug-in
7154 
7155  Features:
7156  *Adds several properties to the 'file' object indicated upload speed, time left, upload time, etc.
7157  - currentSpeed -- String indicating the upload speed, bytes per second
7158  - averageSpeed -- Overall average upload speed, bytes per second
7159  - movingAverageSpeed -- Speed over averaged over the last several measurements, bytes per second
7160  - timeRemaining -- Estimated remaining upload time in seconds
7161  - timeElapsed -- Number of seconds passed for this upload
7162  - percentUploaded -- Percentage of the file uploaded (0 to 100)
7163  - sizeUploaded -- Formatted size uploaded so far, bytes
7164 
7165  *Adds setting 'moving_average_history_size' for defining the window size used to calculate the moving average speed.
7166 
7167  *Adds several Formatting functions for formatting that values provided on the file object.
7168  - SWFUpload.speed.formatBPS(bps) -- outputs string formatted in the best units (Gbps, Mbps, Kbps, bps)
7169  - SWFUpload.speed.formatTime(seconds) -- outputs string formatted in the best units (x Hr y M z S)
7170  - SWFUpload.speed.formatSize(bytes) -- outputs string formatted in the best units (w GB x MB y KB z B )
7171  - SWFUpload.speed.formatPercent(percent) -- outputs string formatted with a percent sign (x.xx %)
7172  - SWFUpload.speed.formatUnits(baseNumber, divisionArray, unitLabelArray, fractionalBoolean)
7173  - Formats a number using the division array to determine how to apply the labels in the Label Array
7174  - factionalBoolean indicates whether the number should be returned as a single fractional number with a unit (speed)
7175  or as several numbers labeled with units (time)
7176  */
7177

7274  // Private: extends the file object with the speed plugin values
7275  SWFUpload.speed.extendFile = function (file, trackingList) {
7276  var tracking;
7277 
7278  if (trackingList) {
7279  tracking = trackingList[file.id];
7280  }
7281 
7282  if (tracking) {
7283  file.currentSpeed = tracking.currentSpeed;
7284  file.averageSpeed = tracking.averageSpeed;
7285  file.movingAverageSpeed = tracking.movingAverageSpeed;
7286  file.timeRemaining = tracking.timeRemaining;
7287  file.timeElapsed = tracking.timeElapsed;
7288  file.percentUploaded = tracking.percentUploaded;
7289  file.sizeUploaded = tracking.bytesUploaded;
7290 
7291  } else {
7292  file.currentSpeed = 0;
7293  file.averageSpeed = 0;
7294  file.movingAverageSpeed = 0;
7295  file.timeRemaining = 0;
7296  file.timeElapsed = 0;
7297  file.percentUploaded = 0;
7298  file.sizeUploaded = 0;
7299  }
7300 
7301  return file;
7302  };
7303 
7304  // Private: Updates the speed tracking object, or creates it if necessary
7305  SWFUpload.prototype.updateTracking = function (file, bytesUploaded) {
7306  var tracking = this.fileSpeedStats[file.id];
7307  if (!tracking) {
7308  this.fileSpeedStats[file.id] = tracking = {};
7309  }
7310 
7311  // Sanity check inputs
7312  bytesUploaded = bytesUploaded || tracking.bytesUploaded || 0;
7313  if (bytesUploaded < 0) {
7314  bytesUploaded = 0;
7315  }
7316  if (bytesUploaded > file.size) {
7317  bytesUploaded = file.size;
7318  }
7319 
7320  var tickTime = (new Date()).getTime();
7321  if (!tracking.startTime) {
7322  tracking.startTime = (new Date()).getTime();
7323  tracking.lastTime = tracking.startTime;
7324  tracking.currentSpeed = 0;
7325  tracking.averageSpeed = 0;
7326  tracking.movingAverageSpeed = 0;
7327  tracking.movingAverageHistory = [];
7328  tracking.timeRemaining = 0;
7329  tracking.timeElapsed = 0;
7330  tracking.percentUploaded = bytesUploaded / file.size;
7331  tracking.bytesUploaded = bytesUploaded;
7332  } else if (tracking.startTime > tickTime) {
7333  this.debug("When backwards in time");
7334  } else {
7335  // Get time and deltas
7336  var now = (new Date()).getTime();
7337  var lastTime = tracking.lastTime;
7338  var deltaTime = now - lastTime;
7339  var deltaBytes = bytesUploaded - tracking.bytesUploaded;
7340 
7341  if (deltaBytes === 0 || deltaTime === 0) {
7342  return tracking;
7343  }
7344 
7345  // Update tracking object
7346  tracking.lastTime = now;
7347  tracking.bytesUploaded = bytesUploaded;
7348 
7349  // Calculate speeds
7350  tracking.currentSpeed = (deltaBytes * 8 ) / (deltaTime / 1000);
7351  tracking.averageSpeed = (tracking.bytesUploaded * 8) / ((now - tracking.startTime) / 1000);
7352 
7353  // Calculate moving average
7354  tracking.movingAverageHistory.push(tracking.currentSpeed);
7355  if (tracking.movingAverageHistory.length > this.settings.moving_average_history_size) {
7356  tracking.movingAverageHistory.shift();
7357  }
7358 
7359  tracking.movingAverageSpeed = SWFUpload.speed.calculateMovingAverage(tracking.movingAverageHistory);
7360 
7361  // Update times
7362  tracking.timeRemaining = (file.size - tracking.bytesUploaded) * 8 / tracking.movingAverageSpeed;
7363  tracking.timeElapsed = (now - tracking.startTime) / 1000;
7364 
7365  // Update percent
7366  tracking.percentUploaded = (tracking.bytesUploaded / file.size * 100);
7367  }
7368 
7369  return tracking;
7370  };
7371  SWFUpload.speed.removeTracking = function (file, trackingList) {
7372  try {
7373  trackingList[file.id] = null;
7374  delete trackingList[file.id];
7375  } catch (ex) {
7376  }
7377  };

7379  SWFUpload.speed.formatUnits = function (baseNumber, unitDivisors, unitLabels, singleFractional) {
7380  var i, unit, unitDivisor, unitLabel;
7381 
7382  if (baseNumber === 0) {
7383  return "0 " + unitLabels[unitLabels.length - 1];
7384  }
7385 
7386  if (singleFractional) {
7387  unit = baseNumber;
7388  unitLabel = unitLabels.length >= unitDivisors.length ? unitLabels[unitDivisors.length - 1] : "";
7389  for (i = 0; i < unitDivisors.length; i++) {
7390  if (baseNumber >= unitDivisors[i]) {
7391  unit = (baseNumber / unitDivisors[i]).toFixed(2);
7392  unitLabel = unitLabels.length >= i ? " " + unitLabels[i] : "";
7393  break;
7394  }
7395  }
7396 
7397  return unit + unitLabel;
7398  } else {
7399  var formattedStrings = [];
7400  var remainder = baseNumber;
7401 
7402  for (i = 0; i < unitDivisors.length; i++) {
7403  unitDivisor = unitDivisors[i];
7404  unitLabel = unitLabels.length > i ? " " + unitLabels[i] : "";
7405 
7406  unit = remainder / unitDivisor;
7407  if (i < unitDivisors.length -1) {
7408  unit = Math.floor(unit);
7409  } else {
7410  unit = unit.toFixed(2);
7411  }
7412  if (unit > 0) {
7413  remainder = remainder % unitDivisor;
7414 
7415  formattedStrings.push(unit + unitLabel);
7416  }
7417  }
7418 
7419  return formattedStrings.join(" ");
7420  }
7421  };
7422 
7423  SWFUpload.speed.formatBPS = function (baseNumber) {
7424  var bpsUnits = [1073741824, 1048576, 1024, 1], bpsUnitLabels = ["Gbps", "Mbps", "Kbps", "bps"];
7425  return SWFUpload.speed.formatUnits(baseNumber, bpsUnits, bpsUnitLabels, true);
7426 
7427  };

7430  return SWFUpload.speed.formatUnits(baseNumber, timeUnits, timeUnitLabels, false);
7431 
7432  };
7433  SWFUpload.speed.formatBytes = function (baseNumber) {

7441 
7442  SWFUpload.speed.calculateMovingAverage = function (history) {
7443  var vals = [], size, sum = 0.0, mean = 0.0, varianceTemp = 0.0, variance = 0.0, standardDev = 0.0;
7444  var i;
7445  var mSum = 0, mCount = 0;
7446 
7447  size = history.length;
7448 
7449  // Check for sufficient data
7450  if (size >= 8) {
7451  // Clone the array and Calculate sum of the values
7452  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
7453  vals[i] = history[i];
7454  sum += vals[i];
7455  }
7456 
7457  mean = sum / size;
7458 
7459  // Calculate variance for the set
7460  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
7461  varianceTemp += Math.pow((vals[i] - mean), 2);
7462  }
7463 
7464  variance = varianceTemp / size;
7465  standardDev = Math.sqrt(variance);
7466 
7467  //Standardize the Data
7468  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
7469  vals[i] = (vals[i] - mean) / standardDev;
7470  }
7471 
7472  // Calculate the average excluding outliers
7473  var deviationRange = 2.0;
7474  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
7475 
7476  if (vals[i] <= deviationRange && vals[i] >= -deviationRange) {
7477  mCount++;
7478  mSum += history[i];
7479  }
7480  }
7481 
7482  } else {
7483  // Calculate the average (not enough data points to remove outliers)
7484  mCount = size;
7485  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
7486  mSum += history[i];
7487  }
7488  }
7489 
7490  return mSum / mCount;
7491  };
7492 
7493 }

7616 // Show/Hide the cancel button
7617 FileProgress.prototype.toggleCancel = function (show, swfUploadInstance) {
7618  this.fileProgressElement.childNodes[0].style.visibility = show ? "visible" : "hidden";
7619  if (swfUploadInstance) {
7620  var fileID = this.fileProgressID;
7621  this.fileProgressElement.childNodes[0].onclick = function () {
7622  swfUploadInstance.cancelUpload(fileID);
7623  return false;
7624  };
7625  }
7626 };
7627 
7628 FileProgress.prototype.appear = function () {
7629  if (this.getTimer() !== null) {
7630  clearTimeout(this.getTimer());
7631  this.setTimer(null);
7632  }
7633 
7634  if (this.fileProgressWrapper.filters) {
7635  try {
7636  this.fileProgressWrapper.filters.item("DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Alpha").opacity = 100;
7637  } catch (e) {
7638  // If it is not set initially, the browser will throw an error. This will set it if it is not set yet.
7639  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.filter = "progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Alpha(opacity=100)";
7640  }
7641  } else {
7642  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.opacity = 1;
7643  }
7644 
7645  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.height = "";
7646 
7647  this.height = this.fileProgressWrapper.offsetHeight;
7648  this.opacity = 100;
7649  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.display = "";
7650 
7651 };
7652 
7653 // Fades out and clips away the FileProgress box.
7654 FileProgress.prototype.disappear = function () {
7655 
7656  var reduceOpacityBy = 15;
7657  var reduceHeightBy = 4;
7658  var rate = 30; // 15 fps
7659 
7660  if (this.opacity > 0) {
7661  this.opacity -= reduceOpacityBy;
7662  if (this.opacity < 0) {
7663  this.opacity = 0;
7664  }
7665 
7666  if (this.fileProgressWrapper.filters) {
7667  try {
7668  this.fileProgressWrapper.filters.item("DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Alpha").opacity = this.opacity;
7669  } catch (e) {
7670  // If it is not set initially, the browser will throw an error. This will set it if it is not set yet.
7671  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.filter = "progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Alpha(opacity=" + this.opacity + ")";
7672  }
7673  } else {
7674  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.opacity = this.opacity / 100;
7675  }
7676  }
7677 
7678  if (this.height > 0) {
7679  this.height -= reduceHeightBy;
7680  if (this.height < 0) {
7681  this.height = 0;
7682  }
7683 
7684  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.height = this.height + "px";
7685  }
7686 
7687  if (this.height > 0 || this.opacity > 0) {
7688  var oSelf = this;
7689  this.setTimer(setTimeout(function () {
7690  oSelf.disappear();
7691  }, rate));
7692  } else {
7693  this.fileProgressWrapper.style.display = "none";
7694  this.setTimer(null);
7695  }
7696 };

7702 /* **********************
7703  Event Handlers
7704  These are my custom event handlers to make my
7705  web application behave the way I went when SWFUpload

7710 function fileQueued(file) {
7711  try {
7712  var progress = new FileProgress(file, this.customSettings.progressTarget);
7713  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "pending" ) );
7714  progress.toggleCancel(true, this);
7715 
7716  } catch (ex) {
7717  this.debug(ex);
7718  }
7719 
7720 }

7722 function fileQueueError(file, errorCode, message) {
7723  try {
7724  if (errorCode === SWFUpload.QUEUE_ERROR.QUEUE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED) {
7725  alert("You have attempted to queue too many files.\n" + (message === 0 ? "You have reached the upload limit." : "You may select " + (message > 1 ? "up to " + message + " files." : "one file.")));
7726  return;
7727  }
7728 
7729  var progress = new FileProgress(file, this.customSettings.progressTarget);
7730  progress.setError();
7731  progress.toggleCancel(false);
7732 
7733  switch (errorCode) {
7734  case SWFUpload.QUEUE_ERROR.FILE_EXCEEDS_SIZE_LIMIT:
7735  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "file_is_too_big" ));
7736  this.debug("Error Code: File too big, File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7737  break;
7738  case SWFUpload.QUEUE_ERROR.ZERO_BYTE_FILE:
7739  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "cannot_upload_zero_bytes" ) );
7740  this.debug("Error Code: Zero byte file, File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7741  break;
7742  case SWFUpload.QUEUE_ERROR.INVALID_FILETYPE:
7743  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "invalid_file_type" ) );
7744  this.debug("Error Code: Invalid File Type, File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7745  break;
7746  default:
7747  if (file !== null) {
7748  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "unhandled_error" ) );
7749  }
7750  this.debug("Error Code: " + errorCode + ", File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7751  break;
7752  }
7753  } catch (ex) {
7754  this.debug(ex);
7755  }
7756 }

7766  } catch (ex) {
7767  this.debug(ex);

7776  we can do is say we are uploading.

7782  catch (ex) {}
7783

7811 function uploadError(file, errorCode, message) {
7812  try {
7813  var progress = new FileProgress(file, this.customSettings.progressTarget);
7814  progress.setError();
7815  progress.toggleCancel(false);
7816 
7817  switch (errorCode) {
7818  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.HTTP_ERROR:
7819  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "upload_error" ) + message );
7820  this.debug("Error Code: HTTP Error, File name: " + file.name + ", Message: " + message);
7821  break;
7822  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.UPLOAD_FAILED:
7823  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "upload_failed" ) );
7824  this.debug("Error Code: Upload Failed, File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7825  break;
7826  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.IO_ERROR:
7827  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "server_io_error" ) ) ;
7828  this.debug("Error Code: IO Error, File name: " + file.name + ", Message: " + message);
7829  break;
7830  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.SECURITY_ERROR:
7831  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "security_error" ) );
7832  this.debug("Error Code: Security Error, File name: " + file.name + ", Message: " + message);
7833  break;
7834  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.UPLOAD_LIMIT_EXCEEDED:
7835  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "upload_limit" ) );
7836  this.debug("Error Code: Upload Limit Exceeded, File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7837  break;
7838  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.FILE_VALIDATION_FAILED:
7839  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "failed_validation" ) );
7840  this.debug("Error Code: File Validation Failed, File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7841  break;
7842  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.FILE_CANCELLED:
7843  /* If there aren't any files left (they were all cancelled) disable the cancel button */
7844  if (this.getStats().files_queued === 0) {
7845  document.getElementById(this.customSettings.cancelButtonId).disabled = true;
7846  }
7847  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "cancelled" ) );
7848  progress.setCancelled();
7849  break;
7850  case SWFUpload.UPLOAD_ERROR.UPLOAD_STOPPED:
7851  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "stopped" ) );
7852  break;
7853  default:
7854  progress.setStatus( ultimix.get_string( "unhandled_error" ) + ": " + errorCode);
7855  this.debug("Error Code: " + errorCode + ", File name: " + file.name + ", File size: " + file.size + ", Message: " + message);
7856  break;
7857  }
7858  } catch (ex) {
7859  this.debug(ex);
7860  }
7861 }
7862 
7863 function uploadComplete(file) {
7864  if (this.getStats().files_queued === 0) {
7865  document.getElementById(this.customSettings.cancelButtonId).disabled = true;
7866  }
7867 }

7997 // top wrapper to prevent multiple inclusion (is this OK?)
7998 (function () { if(jQuery && jQuery.jstree) { return; }
7999  var is_ie6 = false, is_ie7 = false, is_ff2 = false;
8000 
8001 /*
8002  * jsTree core
8003  */
8004 (function ($) {
8005  // Common functions not related to jsTree
8006  // decided to move them to a `vakata` "namespace"
8007  $.vakata = {};
8008  // CSS related functions
8009  $.vakata.css = {
8010  get_css : function(rule_name, delete_flag, sheet) {
8011  rule_name = rule_name.toLowerCase();
8012  var css_rules = sheet.cssRules || sheet.rules,
8013  j = 0;
8014  do {
8015  if(css_rules.length && j > css_rules.length + 5) { return false; }
8016  if(css_rules[j].selectorText && css_rules[j].selectorText.toLowerCase() == rule_name) {
8017  if(delete_flag === true) {
8018  if(sheet.removeRule) { sheet.removeRule(j); }
8019  if(sheet.deleteRule) { sheet.deleteRule(j); }
8020  return true;
8021  }
8022  else { return css_rules[j]; }
8023  }
8024  }
8025  while (css_rules[++j]);
8026  return false;
8027  },
8028  add_css : function(rule_name, sheet) {
8029  if($.jstree.css.get_css(rule_name, false, sheet)) { return false; }
8030  if(sheet.insertRule) { sheet.insertRule(rule_name + ' { }', 0); } else { sheet.addRule(rule_name, null, 0); }
8031  return $.vakata.css.get_css(rule_name);
8032  },
8033  remove_css : function(rule_name, sheet) {
8034  return $.vakata.css.get_css(rule_name, true, sheet);
8035  },
8036  add_sheet : function(opts) {
8037  var tmp = false, is_new = true;
8038  if(opts.str) {
8039  if(opts.title) { tmp = $("style[id='" + opts.title + "-stylesheet']")[0]; }
8040  if(tmp) { is_new = false; }
8041  else {
8042  tmp = document.createElement("style");
8043  tmp.setAttribute('type',"text/css");
8044  if(opts.title) { tmp.setAttribute("id", opts.title + "-stylesheet"); }
8045  }
8046  if(tmp.styleSheet) {
8047  if(is_new) {
8048  document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(tmp);
8049  tmp.styleSheet.cssText = opts.str;
8050  }
8051  else {
8052  tmp.styleSheet.cssText = tmp.styleSheet.cssText + " " + opts.str;
8053  }
8054  }
8055  else {
8056  tmp.appendChild(document.createTextNode(opts.str));
8057  document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(tmp);
8058  }
8059  return tmp.sheet || tmp.styleSheet;
8060  }
8061  if(opts.url) {
8062  if(document.createStyleSheet) {
8063  try { tmp = document.createStyleSheet(opts.url); } catch (e) { }
8064  }
8065  else {
8066  tmp = document.createElement('link');
8067  tmp.rel = 'stylesheet';
8068  tmp.type = 'text/css';
8069  tmp.media = "all";
8070  tmp.href = opts.url;
8071  document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(tmp);
8072  return tmp.styleSheet;
8073  }
8074  }
8075  }
8076  };

8078  // private variables
8079  var instances = [], // instance array (used by $.jstree.reference/create/focused)
8080  focused_instance = -1, // the index in the instance array of the currently focused instance
8081  plugins = {}, // list of included plugins
8082  prepared_move = {}; // for the move_node function
8083 
8084  // jQuery plugin wrapper (thanks to jquery UI widget function)
8085  $.fn.jstree = function (settings) {
8086  var isMethodCall = (typeof settings == 'string'), // is this a method call like $().jstree("open_node")
8087  args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 1),
8088  returnValue = this;
8089 
8090  // if a method call execute the method on all selected instances
8091  if(isMethodCall) {
8092  if(settings.substring(0, 1) == '_') { return returnValue; }
8093  this.each(function() {
8094  var instance = instances[$.data(this, "jstree_instance_id")],
8095  methodValue = (instance && $.isFunction(instance[settings])) ? instance[settings].apply(instance, args) : instance;
8096  if(typeof methodValue !== "undefined" && (settings.indexOf("is_") === 0 || (methodValue !== true && methodValue !== false))) { returnValue = methodValue; return false; }
8097  });
8098  }
8099  else {
8100  this.each(function() {
8101  // extend settings and allow for multiple hashes and $.data
8102  var instance_id = $.data(this, "jstree_instance_id"),
8103  a = [],
8104  b = settings ? $.extend({}, true, settings) : {},
8105  c = $(this),
8106  s = false,
8107  t = [];
8108  a = a.concat(args);
8109  if(c.data("jstree")) { a.push(c.data("jstree")); }
8110  b = a.length ? $.extend.apply(null, [true, b].concat(a)) : b;
8111 
8112  // if an instance already exists, destroy it first
8113  if(typeof instance_id !== "undefined" && instances[instance_id]) { instances[instance_id].destroy(); }
8114  // push a new empty object to the instances array
8115  instance_id = parseInt(instances.push({}),10) - 1;
8116  // store the jstree instance id to the container element
8117  $.data(this, "jstree_instance_id", instance_id);
8118  // clean up all plugins
8119  b.plugins = $.isArray(b.plugins) ? b.plugins : $.jstree.defaults.plugins.slice();
8120  b.plugins.unshift("core");
8121  // only unique plugins
8122  b.plugins = b.plugins.sort().join(",,").replace(/(,|^)([^,]+)(,,\2)+(,|$)/g,"$1$2$4").replace(/,,+/g,",").replace(/,$/,"").split(",");
8123 
8124  // extend defaults with passed data
8125  s = $.extend(true, {}, $.jstree.defaults, b);
8126  s.plugins = b.plugins;
8127  $.each(plugins, function (i, val) {
8128  if($.inArray(i, s.plugins) === -1) { s[i] = null; delete s[i]; }
8129  else { t.push(i); }
8130  });

8190  evnt = new $.Event("before.jstree"),
8191  rlbk = false;

8198  func = func.old;
8199  } while(func);
8200  if(!func) { return; }

8205  }

8210

8213  __callback : function (data) {
8214  this.get_container().triggerHandler( i + '.jstree', { "inst" : this, "args" : args, "rslt" : data, "rlbk" : rlbk });
8215  },
8216  __rollback : function () {
8217  rlbk = this.get_rollback();
8218  return rlbk;
8219  },
8220  __call_old : function (replace_arguments) {
8221  return func.old.apply(this, (replace_arguments ? Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 1) : args ) );
8222  }
8223  }), args);
8224  }
8225 
8226  // return the result
8227  return rslt;
8228  };
8229  $.jstree._fn[i].old = val.old;
8230  $.jstree._fn[i].plugin = pname;
8231  });
8232  },

10024 /*

10027  * Depends on the jquery.cookie plugin
10028  */

10171  drag_start : function (e, data, html) {

10194  }

10204  }

10211  }

10216  if(e.pageX - l < 20) {
10217  if(sli && dir2 === "right") { clearInterval(sli); sli = false; }
10218  if(!sli) { dir2 = "left"; sli = setInterval(function () { $(document).scrollLeft($(document).scrollLeft() - $.vakata.dnd.scroll_spd); }, 150); }
10219  }

10963 /*
10964  * jsTree XML plugin
10965  * The XML data store. Datastores are build by overriding the `load_node` and `_is_loaded` functions.
10966  */
10967 (function ($) {
10968  $.vakata.xslt = function (xml, xsl, callback) {
10969  var rs = "", xm, xs, processor, support;
10970  // TODO: IE9 no XSLTProcessor, no document.recalc
10971  if(document.recalc) {
10972  xm = document.createElement('xml');
10973  xs = document.createElement('xml');
10974  xm.innerHTML = xml;
10975  xs.innerHTML = xsl;
10976  $("body").append(xm).append(xs);
10977  setTimeout( (function (xm, xs, callback) {
10978  return function () {
10979  callback.call(null, xm.transformNode(xs.XMLDocument));
10980  setTimeout( (function (xm, xs) { return function () { $(xm).remove(); $(xs).remove(); }; })(xm, xs), 200);
10981  };
10982  })(xm, xs, callback), 100);
10983  return true;
10984  }
10985  if(typeof window.DOMParser !== "undefined" && typeof window.XMLHttpRequest !== "undefined" && typeof window.XSLTProcessor === "undefined") {
10986  xml = new DOMParser().parseFromString(xml, "text/xml");
10987  xsl = new DOMParser().parseFromString(xsl, "text/xml");
10988  // alert(xml.transformNode());
10989  // callback.call(null, new XMLSerializer().serializeToString(rs));
10990 
10991  }
10992  if(typeof window.DOMParser !== "undefined" && typeof window.XMLHttpRequest !== "undefined" && typeof window.XSLTProcessor !== "undefined") {
10993  processor = new XSLTProcessor();
10994  support = $.isFunction(processor.transformDocument) ? (typeof window.XMLSerializer !== "undefined") : true;
10995  if(!support) { return false; }
10996  xml = new DOMParser().parseFromString(xml, "text/xml");
10997  xsl = new DOMParser().parseFromString(xsl, "text/xml");
10998  if($.isFunction(processor.transformDocument)) {
10999  rs = document.implementation.createDocument("", "", null);
11000  processor.transformDocument(xml, xsl, rs, null);
11001  callback.call(null, new XMLSerializer().serializeToString(rs));
11002  return true;
11003  }
11004  else {
11005  processor.importStylesheet(xsl);
11006  rs = processor.transformToFragment(xml, document);
11007  callback.call(null, $("<div />").append(rs).html());
11008  return true;
11009  }
11010  }

11766 /*

11772 (function ($) {

11861  _fn : {
11862  _types_notify : function (n, data) {

11869  return (!obj || !obj.length) ? false : obj.attr(this._get_settings().types.type_attr) || "default";
11870  },
11871  set_type : function (str, obj) {
11872  obj = this._get_node(obj);
11873  var ret = (!obj.length || !str) ? false : obj.attr(this._get_settings().types.type_attr, str);
11874  if(ret) { this.__callback({ obj : obj, type : str}); }
11875  return ret;
11876  },
11877  _check : function (rule, obj, opts) {
11878  obj = this._get_node(obj);
11879  var v = false, t = this._get_type(obj), d = 0, _this = this, s = this._get_settings().types, data = false;
11880  if(obj === -1) {
11881  if(!!s[rule]) { v = s[rule]; }
11882  else { return; }
11883  }
11884  else {
11885  if(t === false) { return; }
11886  data = s.use_data ? obj.data("jstree") : false;
11887  if(data && data.types && typeof data.types[rule] !== "undefined") { v = data.types[rule]; }
11888  else if(!!s.types[t] && typeof s.types[t][rule] !== "undefined") { v = s.types[t][rule]; }
11889  else if(!!s.types["default"] && typeof s.types["default"][rule] !== "undefined") { v = s.types["default"][rule]; }
11890  }
11891  if($.isFunction(v)) { v = v.call(this, obj); }
11892  if(rule === "max_depth" && obj !== -1 && opts !== false && s.max_depth !== -2 && v !== 0) {
11893  // also include the node itself - otherwise if root node it is not checked
11894  obj.children("a:eq(0)").parentsUntil(".jstree","li").each(function (i) {
11895  // check if current depth already exceeds global tree depth
11896  if(s.max_depth !== -1 && s.max_depth - (i + 1) <= 0) { v = 0; return false; }
11897  d = (i === 0) ? v : _this._check(rule, this, false);
11898  // check if current node max depth is already matched or exceeded
11899  if(d !== -1 && d - (i + 1) <= 0) { v = 0; return false; }
11900  // otherwise - set the max depth to the current value minus current depth
11901  if(d >= 0 && (d - (i + 1) < v || v < 0) ) { v = d - (i + 1); }
11902  // if the global tree depth exists and it minus the nodes calculated so far is less than `v` or `v` is unlimited
11903  if(s.max_depth >= 0 && (s.max_depth - (i + 1) < v || v < 0) ) { v = s.max_depth - (i + 1); }
11904  });
11905  }
11906  return v;
11907  },
11908  check_move : function () {
11909  if(!this.__call_old()) { return false; }
11910  var m = this._get_move(),
11911  s = m.rt._get_settings().types,
11912  mc = m.rt._check("max_children", m.cr),
11913  md = m.rt._check("max_depth", m.cr),
11914  vc = m.rt._check("valid_children", m.cr),
11915  ch = 0, d = 1, t;
11916 
11917  if(vc === "none") { return false; }
11918  if($.isArray(vc) && m.ot && m.ot._get_type) {
11919  m.o.each(function () {
11920  if($.inArray(m.ot._get_type(this), vc) === -1) { d = false; return false; }
11921  });
11922  if(d === false) { return false; }
11923  }
11924  if(s.max_children !== -2 && mc !== -1) {
11925  ch = m.cr === -1 ? this.get_container().find("> ul > li").not(m.o).length : m.cr.find("> ul > li").not(m.o).length;
11926  if(ch + m.o.length > mc) { return false; }
11927  }
11928  if(s.max_depth !== -2 && md !== -1) {
11929  d = 0;
11930  if(md === 0) { return false; }
11931  if(typeof m.o.d === "undefined") {
11932  // TODO: deal with progressive rendering and async when checking max_depth (how to know the depth of the moved node)
11933  t = m.o;
11934  while(t.length > 0) {
11935  t = t.find("> ul > li");
11936  d ++;
11937  }
11938  m.o.d = d;
11939  }
11940  if(md - m.o.d < 0) { return false; }
11941  }
11942  return true;
11943  },
11944  create_node : function (obj, position, js, callback, is_loaded, skip_check) {
11945  if(!skip_check && (is_loaded || this._is_loaded(obj))) {
11946  var p = (typeof position == "string" && position.match(/^before|after$/i) && obj !== -1) ? this._get_parent(obj) : this._get_node(obj),

11966  if(ch + 1 > mc) { return false; }
11967  }
11968  if(s.max_depth !== -2 && md !== -1 && (md - 1) < 0) { return false; }
11969  }

11971  }
11972  }

12961 ultimix.DeleteRecord = function( Selector , Url , Prefix , NotSelectedErrorMessage , ConfirmStrign , Waiting , PackageName , PackageVersion )
12962 {
12963  var CheckBoxSelector = '._' + Prefix + '_item_checkbox';
12964  var DialogBoxSelector;
12965 
12966  if( ultimix.grids.RecordSelectedEx( CheckBoxSelector ) == false )
12967  {
12968  ultimix.std_dialogs.MessageBox( NotSelectedErrorMessage , ultimix.get_string( 'Error' ) , ultimix.std_dialogs.MB_OK | ultimix.std_dialogs.MB_ICONERROR | ultimix.std_dialogs.MB_MODAL );
12969  return;
12970  }
12971 
12972  if( Waiting )
12973  {
12974  DialogBoxSelector = ultimix.std_dialogs.MessageBox( ultimix.get_string( 'wait_please' ) , ultimix.get_string( 'Info' ) , ultimix.std_dialogs.MB_ICONLOADING | ultimix.std_dialogs.MB_MODAL );
12975  }
12976 
12977  var Data;
12978 
12979  Data = ultimix.forms.ExtractFormData( jQuery( CheckBoxSelector ).filter( 'input:checked' ) );
12980  Data[ Prefix + '_context_action' ] = 'delete_record';
12981  Data[ Prefix + '_record_id' ] = -1;
12982  Data[ 'package_name' ] = PackageName;
12983  Data[ 'package_version' ] = PackageVersion;
12984  Data[ 'delete_' + Prefix ] = 1;
12985  Data[ 'ajaxed' ] = 1;
12986 
12987  ultimix.DirectController(
12988  Data ,
12989  function()
12990  {
12991  jQuery( DialogBoxSelector ).dialog( 'close' );
12992  ultimix.ReloadGrid( Selector , true , Url );
12993  } ,
12994  { 'async' : true }
12995  );
12996 }
